&lt;p&gt;Kate McLeod creates solid body care that delivers the most concentrated moisture on earth, harnessing the power of pure plant butters. Our waterless formulas melt nature’s most nourishing ingredients directly into your skin, without dilution or fillers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re best known for The Body Stone™—a moisturizing lotion bar that melts on contact with dry skin, delivering a deep-conditioning treatment that’s clinically proven to boost moisture levels and keep you hydrated for 72 hours.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Warehouse Associate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Position Overview &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a reliable, detail-oriented Warehouse Associate to support our day-to-day fulfillment and warehouse operations. You’ll work closely with our operations team to make sure product moves accurately and efficiently — from receiving and storage through pick, pack, and ship. This is a hands-on role in a small, collaborative environment where your work directly impacts the customer experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive, inspect, and put away inbound shipments from manufacturing and third-party suppliers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support pick and pack operations, ensuring orders are fulfilled accurately according to specs and brand standards&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in staging outbound shipments via small parcel and freight carriers, including cold-chain packing when required&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean, organized, and safe warehouse environment including regular tidying of work areas and common spaces&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support proper storage and rotation of inventory (FIFO) to ensure product integrity&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and maintain shipping supply inventory (boxes, tape, void fill, cold-chain materials, etc.), flagging replenishment needs proactively&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct cycle counts and assist with periodic physical inventory&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flag discrepancies, damages, or quality issues to the operations team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support special projects including retail replenishment, wholesale orders, and promotional kits&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years of warehouse, fulfillment, or production experience (consumer goods or food/beverage a plus)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and commitment to accuracy&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate or learn to operate equipment such as pallet jacks and forklifts&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dependable, adaptable, and willing to take on a variety of tasks&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work independently and as part of a team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working at a physical pace — standing, lifting up to 50 lbs, and moving throughout the warehouse&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible to accommodate shift or schedule changes as needed&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic computer skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
